```{r}
library(quantmod)
from <- c("USD", "EUR", "EUR", "AUD")
to <- c("EUR", "USD", "AUD", "EUR")
Currencies <- getQuote(paste0(from, to, "=X"))




Rates <- Currencies |>  
  tibble::rownames_to_column(var = "Currency") |> 
  dplyr::mutate(Currency = gsub("=X", "", Currency),    # Remove "=X"
         Currency = paste0(substr(Currency, 1, 3), "/", substr(Currency, 4, 6))) |>   # Add "/"
  dplyr::select(Currency, Last)




```

```{r}
#| label: fig-Figure1
#| fig-cap: "Net interest earned through options trading over time, summarised by month"
#| echo: false
#| output: true
#| warning: false
#| message: false
#| cache: false



df1 <- options |> 
  dplyr::mutate(Date = as.Date(Date),
                YearMonth = format(Date, "%Y-%m"),   # Extracting Year-Month from Date
                YearMonth = as.Date(paste(YearMonth, "01", sep = "-"), format = "%Y-%m-%d")) |>
  dplyr::group_by(Year, YearMonth) |> 
  dplyr::summarise(Trades = dplyr::n(),
                   Interest_USD = sum(Sum_Net_Yield_USD, na.rm = TRUE),
                   Group = "Monthly")


df2 <- options |> 
  dplyr::mutate(Date = as.Date(Date),
                YearMonth = format(Date, "%Y-%m"),   # Extracting Year-Month from Date
                YearMonth = as.Date(paste(YearMonth, "01", sep = "-"), format = "%Y-%m-%d")) |>
  dplyr::group_by(Year, YearMonth) |> 
  dplyr::summarise(Trades = dplyr::n(),
                   Interest_USD = max(Cummulative_Net_Earnings_USD),
                   Group = "Accumulated")



df3 <- bind_rows(df1, df2)


ggplot(df3, aes(x = YearMonth, y = Interest_USD, group = Group, color = Group)) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point() +
  labs(x = "", y = "Interest ($US, log-scale)", title = "Monthly Earnings Over Time") +
  #scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(0, max(df3$Interest_USD), by = 100)) +
  scale_y_log10() +  # Adding log scale to y-axis
  annotation_logticks(sides = "lr") +
  scale_x_date(date_breaks = "1 month", date_labels = "%b %Y") +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(legend.title = element_blank(),
        legend.position = "bottom",
        axis.text = element_text(size = 12),
        axis.title = element_text(size = 14), 
        plot.title = element_text(size = 16),
        legend.text = element_text(size = 14))
```

## Weekly Summary

Weekly performance is summarised in @tbl-Table2. Gross interest refers to interest in USD excluding broker fees, while Net Interest shows USD earned with broker fees accounted for. Mean interest per trade shows the average interest earned per trade in percent, while Interest earned refers to the total interest earned in percent for the given timer period. The sum of capital committed shows how much money was committed for option trade in the given time period, and the last column shows the mean capital committed per trade.


```{r}
#| label: tbl-Table2
#| tbl-cap: "Weekly performance of option trades since trading commenced"
#| echo: false
#| output: true
#| warning: false
#| message: false
#| cache: false



opt_week <- options |> 
  dplyr::mutate(Month = as.numeric(format(Date, "%m"))) |>   # Extracting Year-Month from Date
  dplyr::filter(Strategy != "Closing position") |> 
  dplyr::group_by(Year, Week) |> 
  dplyr::summarise(.groups = "drop", # suppresses the annoying grouping message
                   `Available_$` = round(mean(Sum_Capital_USD)),
                   Trades = dplyr::n(),
                   `Gross_Interest_$` = sum(Sum_Gross_Yield_USD, na.rm = TRUE),
                   `Net_Interest_$` = sum(Sum_Net_Yield_USD, na.rm = TRUE),
                   `Mean_Interest/Trade_%` = mean(Sum_Net_interest_pc, na.rm = TRUE),
                   #`Interest_earned_%` = sum(Sum_Net_Yield_USD, na.rm = TRUE)*100/mean(Sum_Capital_USD, na.rm = TRUE),
                   `Interest_earned_%` = `Net_Interest_$` *100 / `Available_$`,
                   `Sum_Committed_$` = sum(Capital_committed_USD, na.rm = TRUE),
                   `Mean_Committed_$` = mean(Capital_committed_USD, na.rm = TRUE))
  #dplyr::arrange(Week) |>  # Sort by Year in descending order
  

opt_week |> 
  knitr::kable(digits = 1) |> 
  kableExtra::kable_styling() |> 
  kableExtra::scroll_box(height = "300px", fixed_thead = TRUE)
```

## Monthly Summary

Monthly performance is summarised in @tbl-Table4. Gross interest refers to interest in USD excluding broker fees, while Net Interest shows USD earned with broker fees accounted for. Mean interest per trade shows the average interest earned per trade in percent, while Interest earned refers to the total interest earned in percent for the given timer period. The sum of capital committed shows how much money was committed for option trade in the given time period, and the last column shows the mean capital committed per trade.

## Investment Performance


```{r}
#| label: tbl-Table8
#| tbl-cap: "Investment performance of bought stocks through options"
#| echo: false
#| output: true
#| warning: false
#| message: false
#| cache: false




perf <- options |> 
  filter(!is.na(Investment_Status)) |>  # Filter out rows with NA in Investment_Status
  group_by(Symbol) |> 
  summarise(Date_Invested = ifelse(any(Investment_Status %in% c("Invested", "Closed") & Investment_Event == "Bought"), min(format(Date, "%Y-%m-%d")), ""),
            Date_Closed = ifelse(any(Investment_Status %in% c("Invested", "Closed") & Investment_Event == "Sold"), max(format(Closing_date, "%Y-%m-%d")), ""),
            Days_Invested = ifelse(is.na(Date_Closed), as.numeric(difftime(Sys.Date(), as.Date(Date_Invested, format = "%Y-%m-%d"), units = "days")), 
                                  as.numeric(difftime(as.Date(Date_Closed, format = "%Y-%m-%d"), as.Date(Date_Invested, format = "%Y-%m-%d"), units = "days"))),
            Days_Closed = ifelse(is.na(Date_Closed), NA, as.numeric(difftime(Sys.Date(), as.Date(Date_Closed, format = "%Y-%m-%d"), units = "days"))),
            Invested_Capital = abs(sum(ifelse(Investment_Event == "Bought", Investment_USD, NA), na.rm = TRUE)),
            Mean_Strike = (mean(Investment_USD[Investment_Event == "Bought"], na.rm = TRUE))*(-1)/100, 
    Contracts = sum(Contracts_n[Investment_Event == "Bought"], na.rm = TRUE),
    Trades = n(),  # Count the number of trades
            Sell_Price = abs(max(ifelse(Investment_Event == "Sold", Investment_USD, NA), na.rm = TRUE)),
            Sell_Profit = Sell_Price - Invested_Capital,
            Earnings = sum(Sum_Net_Yield_USD[Date >= min(Date) & Date <= max(Date)], na.rm = TRUE),
            `Earnings_%` = Earnings *100 / Invested_Capital,
            `Return_$` = Sell_Profit + Earnings,
            `Return_%` = `Return_$` *100 / Invested_Capital) |>
  mutate(Date_Closed = ifelse(is.na(Date_Closed), "ACTIVE", Date_Closed),
         ActiveGroup = ifelse(is.na(Days_Closed), 1, 0)) |>  # Create a flag for active trades
  arrange(as.Date(Date_Invested, format = "%Y-%m-%d"), ActiveGroup) |> 
  select(-Days_Closed, -ActiveGroup)# Exclude the Days_Closed column from the output



perf |>
  knitr::kable(digits = 1) |> 
  kableExtra::kable_styling() |> 
  kableExtra::scroll_box(height = "300px", fixed_thead = TRUE)






```

## Active Swings



```{r}
#| label: tbl-Table12
#| tbl-cap: "Currently active swing trades"
#| echo: false
#| output: true
#| warning: false
#| message: false
#| cache: false



# Active Swings Group by symbol and summarize
swing_active <- swings %>%
  dplyr::filter(Status == "active") |>
  dplyr::mutate(Month = format(Date, "%m")) %>%   # Extracting Year-Month from Date
  dplyr::group_by(Symbol) %>%
  dplyr::summarise(
    Date_Invested = if_else(
      any(Investment_Status %in% c("invested", "closed") & Investment_Event == "bought"),
      min(Date[Investment_Status %in% c("invested", "closed") & Investment_Event == "bought"]),  # Extract the minimum date of buying event
      NA),  # Set to NA if there's no buy event
    Date_Closed = if_else(
      any(Investment_Status %in% c("invested", "closed") & Investment_Event == "sold" ),
      max(Date[Investment_Status %in% c("invested", "closed") & Investment_Event == "sold" ]),  # Extract the maximum date of selling event
      NA),
    Strategy = long_short,
    Mean_Strike = paste0("$", mean(Strike_USD[Investment_Event == "bought"], na.rm = TRUE)),
    Target = paste0("$", Target_strike_USD),
    Trades = sum(Investment_Event == "bought"),
    Shares = sum(shares_n),
    `Invested_$` = sum(Sum_order_USD),
    `Portfolio_%` = sum(Portfolio_pc)
    ) |>
  dplyr::mutate(Date_Closed = ifelse(is.na(Date_Closed), "ACTIVE", Date_Closed)
  ) |>
  dplyr::select(-Date_Closed)


swing_active |>
  knitr::kable(digits = 1) |> 
  kableExtra::kable_styling() |> 
  kableExtra::scroll_box(height = "300px", fixed_thead = TRUE)

```

### Summary by Position

```{r}
#| label: tbl-Table13
#| tbl-cap: "Closed swing trades and performance"
#| echo: false
#| output: true
#| warning: false
#| message: false
#| cache: false


# Closed Swings Group by symbol and summarize
swings_perf <- swings |>
  dplyr::filter(Status %in% c("closed", NA)) |>
  dplyr::mutate(Month = format(Date, "%m"),
                Symbol = as.factor(Symbol)) |>
  dplyr::group_by(Symbol, Campaign) |>
  dplyr::arrange(Date) |>
  dplyr::summarise(
    Date_Invested = min(Date[Investment_Event == "bought"]),  # Extract the minimum date of buying event
    Strategy = first(long_short),  # Assuming 'long_short' is constant within each symbol group
    Mean_Strike = paste0("$", mean(Strike_USD[Investment_Event == "bought"])),
    #Target = paste0("$", Target_strike_USD),
    Trades = sum(Investment_Event == "bought"),
    Shares = sum(shares_n[Investment_Event == "bought"]),
    `Invested_$` = sum(Sum_order_USD[Investment_Event == "bought"]),
    `Portfolio_%` = sum(Portfolio_pc[Investment_Event == "bought"]),
    Date_Closed = max(Date[Investment_Event == "sold"]),  # Extract the maximum date of selling event
    Days = ifelse(is.na(Date_Closed), as.numeric(difftime(Sys.Date(), as.Date(Date_Invested, format = "%Y-%m-%d"), units = "days")), as.numeric(difftime(as.Date(Date_Closed, format = "%Y-%m-%d"), as.Date(Date_Invested, format = "%Y-%m-%d"), units = "days"))),
     `Closing_$` = Sum_order_USD[Investment_Event == "sold"],
    `Dividents_$` = sum(Dividents_USD),
    `Commissions_$` = max(Sum_commission_USD),
    Profit = paste0("$", ifelse(Strategy == "short", (`Closing_$` + `Invested_$` - `Commissions_$` + `Dividents_$`)*(-1), `Closing_$` - `Invested_$` - `Commissions_$` + `Dividents_$`)))
```

# Combined Performance from Options, Stocks, and Swing trades 

\
**Last Weeks Performance Summary:**
\



```{r}
#| label: LastWeeksProfits
#| echo: false
#| output: true
#| warning: false
#| message: false
#| cache: false





prof_week <- dplyr::left_join(opt_week, swings_weekly, by = c("Year", "Week"))
prof_week <- dplyr::left_join(prof_week, stocks_weekly, by = c("Year", "Week" ))

prof_week <- prof_week |>
  dplyr::rename(`Swings_$` = Weekly_Profit,
                `Stocks_$` = Profit,
                `Options_$` = `Net_Interest_$`)  |>
  dplyr::mutate(
    `Swings_$` = replace(`Swings_$`, is.na(`Swings_$`), 0),
    `Stocks_$` = replace(`Stocks_$`, is.na(`Stocks_$`), 0),
    `Options_$` = replace(`Options_$`, is.na(`Options_$`), 0),
    `Sum_Profit_$` = coalesce(`Options_$`, 0) + coalesce(`Swings_$`, 0) + coalesce(`Stocks_$`, 0),
    `Interest_Options_%` = coalesce(`Interest_earned_%`, 0),
    `Interest_Total_%` = `Sum_Profit_$` * 100 / coalesce(`Available_$`, 1) # Dividing by 1 to avoid division by zero
  ) |>
  dplyr::select(Year, Week, `Options_$`, `Swings_$`, `Stocks_$`, `Sum_Profit_$`, `Interest_Options_%`, `Interest_Total_%`)
  



last_week <- prof_week |>
  dplyr::slice(n() - 1) |>
  dplyr::mutate(
    `Swings_$` = replace(`Swings_$`, is.na(`Swings_$`), 0),
    `Stocks_$` = replace(`Stocks_$`, is.na(`Stocks_$`), 0),
    `Options_$` = replace(`Options_$`, is.na(`Options_$`), 0))

last_week |>
  knitr::kable(digits = 1) |> 
  kableExtra::kable_classic(full_width = FALSE)



```

```{r}
    `Options_$` = replace(`Options_$`, is.na(`Options_$`), 0),
    `Sum_Profit_$` = coalesce(`Options_$`, 0) + coalesce(`Swings_$`, 0) + coalesce(`Stocks_$`, 0),
    `Interest_Options_%` = coalesce(`Interest_earned_%`, 0),
    `Interest_Total_%` = `Sum_Profit_$` * 100 / coalesce(`Available_$`, 1) # Dividing by 1 to avoid division by zero
  ) |>
  dplyr::select(Year, `Options_$`, `Swings_$`, `Stocks_$`, `Sum_Profit_$`, `Interest_Options_%`, `Interest_Total_%`)
  



last_year <- prof_year |>
  dplyr::slice(n() - 1) |>
  dplyr::mutate(
    `Swings_$` = replace(`Swings_$`, is.na(`Swings_$`), 0),
    `Stocks_$` = replace(`Stocks_$`, is.na(`Stocks_$`), 0),
    `Options_$` = replace(`Options_$`, is.na(`Options_$`), 0))

last_year |>
  knitr::kable(digits = 1) |> 
  kableExtra::kable_classic(full_width = FALSE)



```
